<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA General Task//EN" "generalTask.dtd">
<task id="task_r3q_fnx_pr">
    <title>Configuring Console Settings</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p><indexterm>help<indexterm>local or hosted</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>console
                        settings<indexterm>configuring</indexterm></indexterm>You can configure how
                information in the <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> console displays, such as the online help version, information density in the
                panel, and the pipeline creation help bar.</p>
        </context>
        <steps id="steps_zgq_dpx_pr">
            <step>
                <cmd>In the top right corner of the <ph
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                    /> console, click <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Help</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Settings</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>In the Settings dialog box, you can configure the following options:</cmd>
                <info>       
                    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_nn5_3px_pr">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.39*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Console Setting</entry>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Display Density</entry>
                                    <entry>Defines the density of the information that displays in
                                        the panel.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Help</entry>
                                    <entry>Defines the help project that <ph
                                            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                                        /> uses:<ul id="ul_pzd_kqx_pr">
                                            <li>Local help - Uses the help project installed with
                                                  <ph
                                                  conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                                                />.</li>
                                            <li>Hosted help - Uses a help project hosted on the
                                                StreamSets website. Hosted help contains the latest
                                                available documentation. Requires an internet
                                                connection.</li>
                                        </ul><p>Default is hosted help. When internet access is not
                                            available, <ph
                                                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                                            /> uses local help. </p><p>Both help projects provide
                                            context-sensitive help.</p></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Hide Pipeline Creation Help Bar </entry>
                                    <entry>Hides the pipeline configuration help bar that displays
                                        by default when a pipeline is incomplete. </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Hide REST Response Menu</entry>
                                    <entry>Hides the REST Response menu so you cannot request REST
                                        API response information.</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
